[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e6
{ Preparing to develop our dark-squared bishop to b4. } 5. Nc3 Bb4
{ Developing the bishop as well as pinning the c3-knight. } 6. Bd2
{ White supports his c3-knight and prevents his queenside structure from ruining in case Black captures with ...Bxc3. }
6... Nc6 { Attacking the d4-knight. } 7. e3 O-O 8. a3
{ White prefers to push our bishop back from its active post on b4 before developing his light-squared bishop. }
8... Be7 9. Be2 d5
{ It is time to start action in the centre. We now threaten to capture with ... Nxd4 followed by ...dxc4. }
10. cxd5 Nxd4 11. exd4 Nxd5 { We have got a nice version of the IQP. } 12. Bf3
{ Pressurizing the knight on d5. } 12... Nb6 { Threatening the d4-pawn. } 13.
Be3 Nc4
{ Attacking both the bishop on e3 and the b2-pawn. This makes sure that we win the bishop pair. }
14. O-O Nxe3 15. fxe3 Bd7
{ Black has developed all his pieces. He has the bishop pair as well as a better pawn structure. This line can be found in Chapter 22. }
