Qxd6 14. a5 Qc5 15. Nb3 Qb4+ 16. Nfd2 Nc6
{ This is the easiest way for Black to continue. We attack the a5-pawn even more and develop our knight at the same time. It is obvious that White's lack of development makes it impossible for him to protect his passed pawns on the queenside.   16...Ba4  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@54@@EndBracket@@ Nabaty,T @@StartBracket@@2688@@EndBracket@@ -Santos Ruiz,M @@StartBracket@@2554@@EndBracket@@ Moscow 2019 }
17. Qb1 Ne4
