1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Bg5
{ The Torre Attack! The fundamental idea behind the London System  3.Bf4  and the Torre Attack  3.Bg5  is the same - to develop the dark-squared bishop out of the pawn chain before playing e2-e3. The only difference is the placement of the Bishop. Based on recent trends, it is clear that the London System has overtaken the Torre Attack and proved itself the stronger choice between the two.  We reply by centralizing our Knight on e4 and then continuing with our development. }
3... Ne4 4. Bf4
{ This is White's main retreat. If we compare this position to the London system, Black's knight is actively placed on e4 instead of f6, which is in Black's favour. }
4... Bf5
{ I recommend this simple approach of developing our light-squared bishop out of the pawn chain before we play e7-e6. Our next moves are easy to play. We want to play e7-e6 followed by Bf8-d6 challenging the white bishop on f4. }
5. e3 { 5.Nbd2  e6  6.e3  Bd6  transposes to the mainline. } 5... e6 6. Nbd2
{ 6.c4?!  going for this break with Black's knight on e4 can be risky due to  6...Bb4+  7.Nfd2   7.Nbd2  is also met by  7...g5!  8.Bg3  h5→  with the idea to play ...h4 when White will have to find good moves to avoid getting into a clear minus position.   8...g4?  does not win a piece for Black due to  9.a3!  ±  7...g5  we start playing against White's dark-squared bishop.  8.Be5  f6  9.Bg3  h5  threatening to trap the bishop with ...h4.  10.f3  Nxg3  11.hxg3  c5!  →  opening up the position as quickly as possible. Black has the bishop pair and the white king's position is slightly shaky which gives Black a nice initiative. }
6... Bd6 7. Nxe4 Bxe4 8. Bd3 { is dubious. Black's correct reaction is, } 8...
Bxf4 9. exf4 { And now } 9... Qf6
{ We put pressure on both the d4 and f4 pawns.   9...Bxf3  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Artemiev, V @@StartBracket@@2716@@EndBracket@@-Caruana, F @@StartBracket@@2835@@EndBracket@@ chess. com INT 2020 }
10. Bxe4 dxe4 11. Ne5 Qxf4 12. O-O O-O
{ White has some compensation for the pawn because of his active knight on e5 and Black's lack of development but still needs to prove it. }
