{ This important move enables Black to win the bishop pair. We exploit the fact that White cannot move his bishop away from d3 as it lead will lead to a loss of a pawn for White. }
11. h3
{ 11.Be2?  falls short to,  11...Bf5  and White loses one of his pawns. } 11...
Nxd3 12. cxd3 Bf5
{ Black is slightly better here due to a better pawn structure. } *

