11. axb5 { is met by } 11... Bxc3 12. bxc3 cxb5
{ Again we plan to play ...f6 next. } 13. Rb1 f6 14. Ng4 Qd7 15. e4 Nc7 16. e5
f5
{ It is important for us to keep our kingside pawn structure intact and not allow exf6. }
17. Ne3
{ 17.Bxa8?!  gives away the valuable light-squared bishop.  17...Nxa8  18.Ne3  Bb7  and it is Black who has a slight edge here despite being an exchange down. The powerful light-squared bishop glares at the weak h1-a8 diagonal. }
