{ This wins the pawn back for White but is inferior due to the simple, } 12...
Nxc6 13. Bxc6 Bb7
{ Of course, we should exchange White's light-squared bishop and take the game to a major pieces endgame where we will have a slight edge due to our extra space on the queenside and chances to create a strong passed pawn there. }
14. Bxb7 Qxb7 15. Qxd2 Rfd8
