10. Nxc4 b5
{ A very strong space seizing move on the queenside exploiting the specific tactical features of the position. }
11. axb5 cxb5 { We don't need to worry about our a5-pawn as it is poisoned. }
12. Ne5
{ 12.Bxa5?  Rxa5!  13.Nxa5  Bb4+  and we get two pieces for the rook.   12.Nxa5?  Nxc3-+ }
12... O-O 13. O-O Bb7
{ Black stands clearly better in this position. We have successfully carried out our strategic break of c6-c5 and have space on the queenside. Next, we can gain further space with ...b4 and play ...Nc6 challenging the e5-knight. 0-1 @@StartBracket@@28@@EndBracket@@ Stefanova,A @@StartBracket@@2410@@EndBracket@@-Kurajica,B @@StartBracket@@2545@@EndBracket@@ Benasque 1997 }
