10. Nxc4
{ White needs to take the pawn immediately, otherwise he will never regain it once we support it with ...b5. }
10... b5 { We continue with our strategy of gaining space on the queenside. }
11. Ne5 Bb7
{ Now we intend to play ...Nd7 next challenging the knight on e5.   11...O-O  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@27@@EndBracket@@ Fabri, L-Urbanek,S @@StartBracket@@2214@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2008 }
12. b3 Nd7 13. Nxd7 Qxd7 14. Bb2
{ It is interesting to note that the White dark-squared bishop has travelled all the way from c1-d2-c3 to b2. We have exploited this waste of moves by White by gaining space on the queenside with a5-b5. }
14... O-O 15. Nd2 a4
{ 15...c5  is very desirable but slightly inferior because White might get some pressure after,  16.dxc5  Bxc5  17.Ne4  Be7  18.Qd4!  f6  19.Nc3 }
16. a3 c5 { Now this is fine as White's b3-pawn hangs. } 17. dxc5 Bxc5 18. Ne4
Be7 19. Qd4 f6
{ Black has successfully broken with c6-c5 and is ready to bring the rooks into the game with ... Rfd8-Rac8. }
