18. b4 { The only challenging try. } 18... Bxe5 19. bxc5
{ White has got a passed pawn but it can be easily tackled by the black pieces. }
19... Qxf3 20. Nxf3 Bc7 { It is important to kick the annoying a5-bishop. } 21.
Bc3 O-O 22. Nd4 Rfc8
{ The c5-pawn is about to fall and it is wise for White to simplify the position with, }
23. Nxb5 Nxc5
{ Black is a pawn up but with precise play, White can equalize.  24.Nxc7  Rxc7  25.Be5!  pushing the rook away from the 7th rank so that White can manage to win the a7-pawn.  Rcc8  26.Bd4  Nb3  27.Rxc8+  Rxc8  28.Bxa7=  and we reach a completely drawish endgame. }
