{ With the idea to play ...Bc6, Black has strong compensation for the exchange. After reaching the c6 square, both our bishops will have strong diagonals to play on and our knight is already well placed on c3. White's a2-pawn is hanging for the moment. It is also important to note that White cannot capture our b7-pawn because of the fork on e2. }
