{ With this move, White gains space in the centre and makes sure @@StartBracket@@with further moves@@EndBracket@@ that Black will not be able to break with ...c5. But White in turn hands over the d5 square outpost to us permanently which more than compensates for not being able to get in the ...c5 break. }
10... Nd5 11. Be4 Nxc3
{ Trading pieces is favourable for Black as White has the space advantage.   Another decent alternative for Black to play is  11...N7b6  12.O-O  Be7  Black would like to play ...h6 followed by O-O.  13.Nxd5  Bxd5  14.Be3  h6=  followed by O-O next gives Black a fine position. White has more space in the centre but Black has a firm outpost on the d5-square maintaining the balance. This position is quite similar to the mainline where the light-squared bishops are missing from the board. }
