8. axb5 axb5 9. Rxa8 Bxa8 10. e5 h6 11. Bd2 Nd5 12. Nxb5
{ White has managed to recover his pawn back but has conceded other things to us. Black now has a permanent outpost on d5 and the d4 pawn can be a target. Our light-squared bishop is also well placed on the h1-a8 diagonal. }
12... Nb6
{ Black now threatens to play ...Qd7, kicking the b5-knight back and then exchanging on f3 followed by capturing the d4-pawn. }
13. b3 cxb3 14. Qxb3 Be7
{ Black will O-O next and maintain at least a slight edge because of his positional advantages @@StartBracket@@an outpost on the d5 square, control of the h1-a8 diagonal and White's backward d4-pawn@@EndBracket@@. }
