{ A strong tactical novelty. One should remember this tactical idea as this pattern might reoccur!   11...Bxc3+  0-1 @@StartBracket@@44@@EndBracket@@ Løvås,R @@StartBracket@@1690@@EndBracket@@ -Volkov,A @@StartBracket@@1796@@EndBracket@@ ICCF 2017 @@EndBracket@@ }
12. Qxb4 Nc2+ 13. Kd2 Nxb4 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Bxg7 Rg8 16. Bh6 Bd7
{ After some forced moves Black has come out on top. We stand slightly better because of the better coordination between our pieces. }
