11. Bd2
{ This is the most popular move in this position, played by the likes of Anand, Kramnik, Ivanchuk. White develops his bishop and intends to follow it up with Ra1-c1. There are many ways for Black to continue here, I prefer to fianchetto our light-squared bishop this time with, }
11... b6
{ This not only supports our bishop on c5 in case White plays Ra1-c1, but also prevents White from playing a4-a5. }
12. Bd3
{ 12.Ng5  can be met with  12...Na5  13.Ba2  Bb7=  Preventing White from achieving his aim of Ne4. Black is ready to connect his rooks next by playing ...Ke7. Then the next step would be to bring the rooks into the game on the d- and c-files. Black is fine in this position. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@39@@EndBracket@@ Smejkal,J @@StartBracket@@2560@@EndBracket@@-Huebner,R @@StartBracket@@2595@@EndBracket@@ Rio de Janeiro 1979 }
