9. Qe2
{ The most popular move in this position for White. The white queen is usually well placed on e2, supporting the advance e3-e4. He also frees the d1 square for the rook. }
9... cxd4 10. Rd1
{ The point of White's previous move. White brings his rook on the open file and makes sure that he is able to recover his pawn.   10.exd4?!  offers no compensation for White after,  10...Nxd4  11.Nxd4  Qxd4  12.Rd1  Qg4  White lacks a clear compensation for the pawn. }
10... e5
