12... O-O 13. Bxc4 Rd8
{ 13...Qxg2?  is now very bad for Black due to,  14.O-O-O  and Black will have troubles on the g-file }
14. Qe3 Bd7
{ Black prepares 15...Nc6, thus finishing the development and connecting the rooks. }
15. O-O-O { this was an interesting new try by Carlsen. } 15... Nc6
{ The idea behind Black's previous move. Black develops the knight and challenges the knight on d4 at the same time. }
16. Bb3 Be8
{ This backward bishop move exerts pressure on the d4 knight. Black is already intending to exchange on d4 now thus forcing White to recapture with the c-pawn at some point. This opens up the c-file which is in Black’s favour. }
17. Nxc6 Bxc6 18. h4 { White plans to activate his kingside rook with Rh3-g3. }
18... Qf6
{ It's better to move the queen from the g-file. Black also intends to exchange on d1 followed by bringing the other rook to d8. }
19. Rh3 { Now simple for Black was to play another prophylactic move, } 19...
Kh8
