{ It is time to take a stock of the position on the board. White, for the moment, is 2 pawns down but has the lead in development. White is already threatening to grab both Black's d4 and c4-pawns, while our f6 knight is pinned as well. This sharp situation requires sharp play, so it is vital to remember the correct continuation for Black. }
