10. Ne4 Be7 11. exf6 gxf6 12. Bh4
{ Another important position of this line. White has managed to win a piece using tactics, but Black on the other hand, has gained 3 important pawns. His pawns on c4 and d4 are well advanced and limit white's pieces. Another very important concession that White made in the process of winning the piece is that he committed his king on the queenside where it is vulnerable. One of Black's main strategies from this position is to create play against the white king. Now Black has 3 moves that he has tried in practice and according to me, the simplest to understand and play is, }
