15... O-O
{ With this Black completes his development and is all set to take action on the queenside. }
16. Be2 Qc8+
{ The idea is to move the d7-bishop without exchanging the queens. } 17. Kb1
Bf5 18. g4 Bg6 19. Ka1 Qe6
{ This is one of the best squares for the black queen in this position. Now White can liquidate into an equal endgame after, }
20. Nxf6+ Bxf6 21. Bxf6 Qxf6 22. f4 Nxg4 23. Bxg4 Qxd4 24. Rxd4 Rad8
