12. Rc1
{ 12.Bb5+  should be met by,  12...Ke7   not,  12...Bd7??  due to,  13.Rc1+-  13.Rc1  Qa5  transposes. }
12... Qa5 { White can also improve the position of his king with, } 13. g3
{ Now Black must focus on completing his queenside development with, } 13...
Bd7
{ Black prepares 14...Nc6.   Intending to bring the rook to  d8  is not so strong here due to,  13...Ke7?!  14.Kg2  Rd8  15.Re1!  White's idea of Nd4-f5 is very strong to defend against.  15...Nc6  16.Nf5+!  exf5  17.exf5+  Ne5  18.Qh5  Kd6  N   18...Rf8  19.f4+-  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@30@@EndBracket@@ Rustemov, A @@StartBracket@@2537@@EndBracket@@ -Neubauer, M @@StartBracket@@2431@@EndBracket@@ Germany 2012  19.Bxf7  White threatens Qh6 and has a very strong attack. }
14. Kg2 Nc6 15. Nb5 { should be met by, } 15... Ne5
{ Attacking both the bishop on c4 and the knight on b5. } 16. Qd6
{ leads to a forced but pretty draw! } 16... Bxb5 17. Bxb5+ Qxb5 18. Rc7 Ng6
{ 18...Nd7??  would be a losing mistake due to,  19.Rb1  Qa4  20.Rb4+-  when the black queen will be forced to abandon the support of his d7 knight. }
19. Rd1
{ It seems that the White major pieces have caught the black king in a permanent cage. But, Black has a plan to get out of it. }
19... h5
{ The idea behind this move is to free the h7 square for the h8 rook. Once the black rook stands on h7, the black queen will be free to move @@StartBracket@@for example...Qb6@@EndBracket@@ as there will be no mate after Qd7+ @@StartBracket@@the f7-pawn is now protected by the h7 rook@@EndBracket@@. }
20. a4 Qxa4 21. Rd7 Nf4+ { This is the equalizer for Black. } 22. Kg1
{ 22.Qxf4  Qxd7  23.Rxd7  Kxd7  24.Qxf6  Rhf8=  is an equal endgame.   22.gxf4  leads to a perpetual after,  22...Qxe4+  23.Kf1  Qh1+  24.Ke2  Qe4+=  25.Kd2?  does not work due to,  25...Qd5+  exchanges queens giving Black a winning advantage. }
22... Nh3+ 23. Kg2
{ 23.Kf1  allows the exchanges of queens with,  23...Qa6+-+ } 23... Nf4+
{ and the game soon ended in a perpetual. ½-½ @@StartBracket@@29@@EndBracket@@ Shimanov,A @@StartBracket@@2639@@EndBracket@@-Khairullin,I @@StartBracket@@2657@@EndBracket@@ Legnica 2013 }
