26. Rb1+ Qb5 27. Rxb5+ Kxb5
{ Black has two rooks for White's queen. White is going to win the e5-pawn on the next move when the number of pawns will be equal for both sides. The exposed black king ensures that White will find a perpetual comfortably in the upcoming moves. }
