16. b3 { and now, } 16... b5 { with a completely equal endgame. For example, }
17. c5
{ 17.cxb5?!  could be a bit risky as after  17...axb5=+  Black will play ...b4 freezing White's queenside pawns, when only Black can be better. }
17... Bb7 18. Bxb7 Nxb7 19. b4 Rhc8 20. a4 d6 21. cxd6+
{ 21.axb5  also leads to equality after  21...dxc5  22.bxc5  Nxc5  23.Rdb1  axb5=  and the game will end in a draw. }
21... Nxd6 22. axb5 Nxb5 23. Nxb5 Rxb5
{ all the pawns on the queenside are exchanged and the game will end in a draw. }
