Bxc5 5. Nf3 O-O 6. e3
{ Again,  6.Bg5?  is bad due to,  6...Qb6!  attacking both f2 and b2. } 6... b6
{ our idea is to fianchetto the light-squared bishop and go for the ...d5 break.   6...d5  is another possible alternative if you want to play with an Isolated Queen's Pawn.  7.cxd5  exd5  8.Be2  Nc6  we enter a typical IQP position. }
