{ is inferior due to, } 9... dxc4 10. Bxc4 Nbd7 11. Bb2 a6 12. a4 Qb8
{ A nice multi-purpose move. Our main idea is to play ...Ng4 creating threats on the kingside and provoking weaknesses in White's camp. If White prevents it then we also have another plan of playing ...Bc6 followed by ... Qb7 creating pressure on the long diagonal h1-a8. After getting in ...Qb7 we can also plan to play b7-b5 and kick the bishop from c4. }
