17. Bxc3 Qd8 18. Qc4 Ra7 { Preventing Nc7+. } 19. Qd4 Ra8 20. Nb6
{ White decides to go for the a8-rook.   20.Qc4  Ra7=  leads to a repetition. }
20... axb5 21. Nxa8 Nc6 22. Qd2 Qxa8 23. Bxb5 Qa7
{ An important intermediate move preventing White from 0-0. Next Black will focus on developing his kingside. I believe Black has slightly better chances in this position as our pieces will come out quickly and coordinate well to put White under some pressure. }
