{ White ignores the threat to the e4-pawn hoping to create pressure on the e-file in the near future. }
8... g6
{ 8...Nxe4  is completely possible but I don't like the position after,  9.Bc4  g6  10.Qe2  f5   10...Nf6?  leads us into the same tactical trap that we see in the  8.Bc4  variation.  11.Bf4!  Ra6  12.Nxd6  11.Ng5  Bg7  12.O-O  O-O  13.Re1  Initially the engines prefer this position for Black. But analysing for a while I concluded that it is not so easy to play here for Black because of the pressure on the e-file. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@39@@EndBracket@@ Demidov,M @@StartBracket@@2534@@EndBracket@@ -Salman,P @@StartBracket@@2197@@EndBracket@@ Moscow 2017 }
9. Bc4
