13. Bf1 Bd7
{ Now Black threatens to play ...Ra5 followed by taking the a4-pawn when the knight on b5 falls and we will be a clear pawn up. Another idea is to play ...Ne8 when we can aim to exchange the b5 knight with ...Nc7 or by playing ...f5 weakening the d5-pawn. }
