Bxf3
{ and Black has a very strong compensation for the exchange. White's king is in the centre and will face problems. Black's bishops are strong too and we can try to create threats on the c-file. A sample variation might be,  17.Rg1  Nb4  18.Qd2  Qc7  with the double threat of ... Nc2+ and ...Qxh2.  19.Rg3!  Nc2+  20.Kf1  Nxa3  21.bxa3  Bd5=  The material is more or less balanced as the doubled a-pawns do not count for much. }
