13. Be3 Ng4
{ Now there are two ways for White to defend the bishop on e3 with the queen, but there is not a big difference between them as our response is going to be the same. }
14. d6
{ this advance is surely premature as it opens up the diagonal for our sleeping bishop on b7. }
14... Qe6 15. O-O Nxe3 16. fxe3 Nc6
{ bringing our pieces in the game is more important than grabbing the e3-pawn. }
17. Re1 Ne5
{ Black has a nice initiative here because of our strong double bishops. White's pawn on d6 is also weak. }
