{ it might seem counter-intuitive to give a check with the queen instead of the rook. However, our queen is more effective if White blocks the check with Be3.   12...Re8+?!  seems like the most natural move to make here, but after,  13.Be3  Ng4  14.O-O!  White sacrifices a pawn for the initiative.  14...Nxe3  15.fxe3  Rxe3  16.Qd2  Followed by Rae1, when White has more pieces on the kingside while our pieces are stuck on the queenside. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Fier,A @@StartBracket@@2628@@EndBracket@@-Rambaldi,F @@StartBracket@@2513@@EndBracket@@ Biel 2015 }
