{ covering the c7 square and opening up the a1-h8 diagonal for the bishop. }
19. Qc2 Qe4 { If, } 20. Qxe4 Rxe4 21. a5 Ba6 22. Rd1 Bxb5 23. Rxd5
{ now Black has the strong move, } 23... Bd4
{ blocking the white rook's path back home. Black's active bishops and rook on e4 provide good compensation that is sufficient for equality. }
