10... Rxb6 11. Bc3 { and now it is time to seize the d5 square by, } 11... Nb4
{ kicking the white queen back. } 12. Qd2 Bb7 13. a3 Rd6
{ improving the position of our rook } 14. Qe3+ Re6 15. Qd2 Nd5 16. Ba5 Qb8
{ The queen is well placed on b8 and Black plans to play Nd5-f6 followed by d7-d5 next with a nice control in the centre. Black is slightly better.   16...Qa8  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@39@@EndBracket@@ Gallagher,J @@StartBracket@@2524@@EndBracket@@ -Degraeve,J @@StartBracket@@2589@@EndBracket@@ Metz 2001 }
