11. Qc2 Nxc3 12. Bd2
{ White is again all set to regain his material, but Black escapes with, }
12... Qa4
{ utilizing the unprotected White queen on c2 to get away from the pin. } 13.
b3 Qe4+ 14. Qxe4 Nxe4 15. Rc1 Bb7 16. Bc4 Ra8
{ attacking the a2-pawn in order to provoke weaknesses on the queenside.   16...d6  1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@17@@EndBracket@@ Gavrilov,A @@StartBracket@@2498@@EndBracket@@-Nagy,G @@StartBracket@@2433@@EndBracket@@ Schwäbisch Gmünd 2017 }
