{ Hoping to end the quickly with Ra8+ :@@EndBracket@@   27.Kf1  is an attempt to go the  g1  square, which will help White to cover the entry points on the h-file.  27...Rh4  28.Rxh4  Qxh4  29.Kg1  Bd4  Black nevertheless creates continuous threats.  30.Ne4  Qg4  31.b4  Nh4  32.g3  Nf3+  33.Kg2  Nh4+=  and the game would end in a perpetual.   27.Rh3  Rxd5  28.Kf1  Qc4+  29.Kg1  Re5=∞  Black has a powerful compensation for the exchange because of his active pieces. }
