{ Black has just one pawn for the exchange which in itself does not provide good compensation, but if we carefully look at the position, we can see that White's pawn on d5 is weak and his king is very insecure on e1. These two factors combined with Black's active and well-placed pieces provide a nice compensation to Black. }
