14. Nge2 e6 15. Rhf1 Bxc5 16. Nxe4 Be3+ 17. Kb1 Bc6
{ The two bishops create a havoc in White's camp. } 18. N2c3 Rad8 19. Rde1 Bd4
20. Ba4 { The losing move! Can you spot the win for Black? } 20... Bxc3 21.
Nxc3 Nf3 { with double threats to win an exchange. } 22. Bxc6 Nd2+ 23. Kc1 Nxf1
24. Rxf1 Kxc6 { Black is a clear exchange up and won the game comfortably. }
25. Rxf7 Rhf8 26. Rxf8 Rxf8 27. Kd2 Rf3 28. Ne2 e5 29. a4 h5 30. h4 a6 31. Ke1
