{ In this game we will learn how to exploit weaknesses on White's queenside in a variation of the Catalan. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Nf3 dxc4 5. Bg2 c6 6. a4 Bb4+ 7. Nc3 O-O 8. O-O
Nbd7 9. Qc2 a5 { a good prophylactic move preventing future a5 by White. } 10.
Rd1 Qe7 { Black is preparing for the ...e5 break. } 11. Na2 Bd6 12. Qxc4 e5
