27. b3 Rb4 28. Kf1 b6
{ the difference between the activity of both sides pieces is very apparant. }
29. f3 Rc7 30. Bxe6+ Nxe6 31. Rd3 Rc1+ 32. Kf2 Nc5 33. Rd6 Ke7 34. Rd5 Rd1 35.
e4 g4 { shattering White's pawn structure. } 36. Ke2 Rh1 37. fxg4 Rxh2+ 38. Ke3
